Some examples of bug reports written by me. 1st - Functional bug, 2nd - UI/UX bug, 3rd - Logic bug, 4th - User Experience bug, 5th - Compatibility bugs, 6th - Performance bug 


#1 Functional bug
Title: Language changes are not completely supported
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the link
2. Change the language to Greek and refresh the page
3. Navigate to the "Discovery" page
4. Explore the behavior of the website
Actual result: On the landing page, language changes are applied inconsistently. Titles are in English, and paragraphs are in the set language. Page "Discover" always appears in English. 
The home page doesn't support language changes
Expected result: Language change should change across the page and be consistent
Severity: High
Priority: High
Attachment: Screenshot/video recording attached

#2 UI/UX bug
Title: Toggle password visibility is missing
Steps to reproduce:
  1. Open the link
  2. Fill the password field with the data "secret_sauce"
Actual result: User is unable to check the spelling of the password
Expected result: There should be an eye icon inside the password field that allows the user to toggle password visibility 
Severity: Low
Priority: Medium
Attachment: Screenshot/video recording attached

#3 Logic bug
Title: The Website accepts future birth year
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the link
2. Go to Sign Up
3. Fill the birth date fields with data: Month: November, Day:23rd, Year:2028
4. Click on the "Submit" button
Actual result: The system allows the user to select the birth year in the future (e.g., 2028)
Expected result: The system should reject selecting a future date as a valid date of birth and display an error message
Severity: Medium
Priority: Medium
Attachment: Screenshot/video recording attached

#4 User experience bug
Title: After successfully signing up, the page doesn't directly redirect to the profile page
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the link
2. Go to the Sign Up page
3. Fill the credentials with the valid data
4. Click on the "Sign Up" button - no response
5. Click on the "Sign Up" button a second time
6. The error message "Email already exists" appears
7. Go back to the landing page
8. Click on Login
9. Fill fields with the same valid data
10. Click on the "Login" button - redirects to the Profile page
Actual result: After successfully signing up, the user needs to go back to the landing page and log in manually to access the profile page
Expected result: The Sign Up page should automatically redirect to the profile page after successful signing up
Severity: High
Priority: High
Attachment: Screenshot/video recording attached

#5 Compatibility bugs
Title: Website opens zoomed in on mobile devices
Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the website on mobile
2. Observe the page
Actual result: The web page appears zoomed in
Expected result: The website should adjust the screen resolution and display the page content fully
Environment: iPhone 13 ProMax, Google Chrome extension v. 393
Severity: High
Priority: High
Attachment: Screenshot/video recording attached

#6 Performance bug
Title: Game performance is not consistent
Steps to reproduce: 
1.	Open the link
2.	Click on Play now
3.	Open the DevTools
4.	Navigate to the Performance tab
5.	Click on the recording button(play icon at upper lift corner)
6.	Play for 20-30 sec
7.	Stop the record
Actual result: The Game has noticeable fps drops and delayed loading
Expected result: The game should have stable fps and frame rate, and load accordingly 
Severity: High
Priority: High
Attachment: Screenshot/video recording attached
